NYSERDA Offshore Case Study
===========================
Restart from an 11-month simulation performed by Optis et al 2021
("New methods to improve the vertical extrapolation of near-surface offshore wind speeds,"
submitted to Wind Energy Science)

Required symlinks
-----------------

- executables:
ln -sf $WRFDIR/run/[aBbCcEGgHikLmopRStUV]* .
ln -sf $WRFDIR/run/real.exe .
ln -sf $WRFDIR/run/wrf.exe .

- real data:
cp -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/met_data/2020_05/geo_em.d??.nc .
cp -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/met_data/2020_05/met_em.d??.2020-05-15_*.nc .
cp -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/met_data/2020_05/met_em.d??.2020-05-16_00:00:00.nc .

- simulation restarts:
cp -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrfrst_d??_2020-05-15_12:00:00* .


Unused real.exe outputs from Mike
---------------------------------

- initial/boundary condiitons
ln -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrfinput_d01
ln -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrfbdy_d01

- lower boundary data (w/ sst_update=1):
ln -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrflowinp_d01
ln -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrflowinp_d02

- spectral nudging:
ln -s /scratch/moptis/wrf_runs/prod-midatlantic/WPS1/WRF1/2020/05/wrffdda_d01

